The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for real-time tool wear monitoring in CNC machines. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also involves data processing and optimization, which could be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE). The use of force measurements and multivariate analysis suggests the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY).
